currentPositions.description:
The KNCV is a non-profit learned society in the Netherlands of chemists, life scientists, process technologists and (bio-)molecular scientists. 
Our members bring the variety and richness of the molecular field to life and operate in business, education and government or study at universities or institutions of higher education in The Netherlands.

Responsible for:
* day-to-day activities of the Society. We enhance the visibility of chemists and life scientists and how their work impacts society;
* design, develop en implement plans for strategic development;
* managing and developing a high-performance team as well as working with volunteers; 
* develop annual budgets and meet financial and other resource planning objectives; 
* reporting to the Board on a regular basis;
* maintain relationships with member societies in the molecular community, both foreign and domestic;
* creating exciting events to bring members together;
* representing the Society, including promotion at events and on social media platforms
